<subSubSection id="C3339DA8FFA4FF92AF5BE925FDA7FE70" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="354" pageId="14" pageNumber="353" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B96CE23FFA4FF93AF5BE925FF04FE34" blockId="14.[121,225,366,391]" box="[121,225,366,391]" pageId="14" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis id="B95D1231FFA4FF93AF5BE925FF04FE34" box="[121,225,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="353">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96CE23FFA4FF92AF5BE9EAFDA7FE70" blockId="14.[121,1089,417,478]" lastBlockId="15.[121,1089,147,451]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="354" pageId="14" pageNumber="353">
<taxonomicName id="4C29B5A0FFA4FF93AF5BE9EAFEC6FE08" authorityName="Giron &amp; Franz" authorityYear="2010" box="[121,291,417,443]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Apodrosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="353" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="artus">
<emphasis id="B95D1231FFA4FF93AF5BE9EAFEC6FE08" box="[121,291,417,443]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="353">Apodrosus artus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the combination of a relatively narrow body shape (3.2-times longer than wide), the absence of a carinate striped projection on the posterior margin of the epistome, an antennal scape that surpasses the posterior margin of eyes, an only slightly produced metasternum (in lateral profile), an irregularly colored vestiture composed of yellowish brown, black and green, iridescent (yellowish, reddish) scales and with recurvate, lanceolate brown setae, and an aedeagus apex with a mesal, laterally acutely offset projection. This species may be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C29B5A0FFA5FF92AF5BE90AFEE1FEE8" authorityName="Girón &amp; Franz" authorityYear="2010" box="[121,260,321,347]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Apodrosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andersoni">
<emphasis id="B95D1231FFA5FF92AF5BE90AFF6FFEE8" box="[121,138,321,347]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="354">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95D1231FFA5FF92AFBEE90AFEE1FEE8" box="[156,260,321,347]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="354">andersoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its more narrow body shape and parallel-sided elytra with recurvate setae, and from 
<taxonomicName id="4C29B5A0FFA5FF92AE0FE92FFE38FECE" authorityName="Girón &amp; Franz" authorityYear="2010" box="[301,477,356,382]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Apodrosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="earinusparsus">
<emphasis id="B95D1231FFA5FF92AE0FE92FFEDBFECD" box="[301,318,356,382]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="354">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95D1231FFA5FF92AE6FE92FFE38FECE" box="[333,477,356,381]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="354">earinusparsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a lighter coloration and elytra with recurvate setae. 
<taxonomicName id="4C29B5A0FFA5FF92AF5BE9CDFEB4FE13" authorityName="Girón &amp; Franz" authorityYear="2010" box="[121,337,390,416]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Apodrosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridium">
<emphasis id="B95D1231FFA5FF92AF5BE9CDFEB4FE13" box="[121,337,390,416]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="354">Apodrosus viridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a similar body shape but lacks the irregularly colored scale coverage and presents erect elytral setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
