<subSubSection id="C3339DA8FFBAFF8DAF5BED25FEBBFA53" pageId="16" pageNumber="355" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B96CE23FFBAFF8DAF5BED25FF0DFA3B" blockId="16.[121,232,1390,1416]" box="[121,232,1390,1416]" pageId="16" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis id="B95D1231FFBAFF8DAF5BED25FF0DFA3B" box="[121,232,1390,1416]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="355">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96CE23FFBAFF8DAF5BEDE9FEBBFA53" blockId="16.[121,1089,1442,1504]" pageId="16" pageNumber="355">
Named in reference to the narrow body shape, with Latin adjective 
<taxonomicName id="4C29B5A0FFBAFF8DAC46EDE8FC7FFA0F" authorityName="Giron &amp; Franz" authorityYear="2010" box="[868,922,1443,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Apodrosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="artus">
<emphasis id="B95D1231FFBAFF8DAC46EDE8FC7FFA0F" box="[868,922,1443,1468]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="355">artus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
meaning “narrow” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB8B3D2FFBAFF8DAF9CED8EFEB7FA53" author="Brown, R. W." bookContentInfo="882 pp." box="[190,338,1477,1504]" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, DC" pageId="16" pageNumber="355" refId="ref39480" refString="Brown, R. W. (1956) Composition of scientific words, revised edition. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, DC, 882 pp." title="Composition of scientific words, revised edition" type="book" year="1956">Brown 1956</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3339DA8FFBAFF8CAF5BEE45FD67FF62" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="356" pageId="16" pageNumber="355" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B96CE23FFBAFF8DAF5BEE45FEF8F99B" blockId="16.[121,285,1550,1576]" box="[121,285,1550,1576]" pageId="16" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis id="B95D1231FFBAFF8DAF5BEE45FEF8F99B" box="[121,285,1550,1576]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="355">Natural history</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96CE23FFBAFF8DAF5BEE09FBA5F9CC" blockId="16.[121,1089,1602,1664]" pageId="16" pageNumber="355">
<taxonomicName id="4C29B5A0FFBAFF8DAF5BEE09FEC6F9EF" authorityName="Giron &amp; Franz" authorityYear="2010" box="[121,291,1602,1628]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Apodrosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="artus">
<emphasis id="B95D1231FFBAFF8DAF5BEE09FEC6F9EF" box="[121,291,1602,1628]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="355">Apodrosus artus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known to occur in the Central Cordillera at an altitudinal range of 1000–1150 m, in the La Vega province of the Dominican Republic, northeast of Pico
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96CE23FFBBFF8CAF5BE8DFFD67FF62" blockId="17.[121,1089,147,209]" pageId="17" pageNumber="356">
Duarte, the highest elevation of the Hispaniola (
<figureCitation id="1312D2A6FFBBFF8CADB9E8D8FCE4FF1D" box="[667,769,147,174]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="61.[121,154,1637,1659]" captionTargetBox="[125,1085,146,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[125,1085,146,1615]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Fig. 18. Occurrences of Apodrosus species in (A) the Bahamas (Grand Bahama and Andros Island) and (B) Hispaniola, Mona Island, and the Turks and Caicos Islands." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3764604" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3764604/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="356">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
). Adults have been taken on guava (
<taxonomicName id="4C29B5A0FFBBFF8CAFE8E8FDFE14FF63" authority="Linnaeus" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[202,497,182,208]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Psidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="17" pageNumber="356" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="guajava">
<emphasis id="B95D1231FFBBFF8CAFE8E8FDFE9AFF63" box="[202,383,182,208]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="356">Psidium guajava</emphasis>
Linnaeus
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C29B5A0FFBBFF8CAEDEE8FCFD93FF62" box="[508,630,183,209]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="17" pageNumber="356" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Myrtaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
